# Python Standards

## Project Structure
- Tests in `tests/` directory
- Dependencies in `requirements.txt` or `pyproject.toml`
- Static files in `static/` directory
- Use virtual environments (usually: `pyenv activate <env_name>`)

## Code Style
- Black formatting (88 char line length)
- PEP 8 naming: `snake_case` functions/variables, `PascalCase` classes, `UPPER_CASE` constants
- Absolute imports over relative imports

## Type Hints
- Type all function parameters and return values
- Use `Optional[Type]` for nullable types
- Define custom types in `types.py`
- Use `Protocol` for duck typing

## Documentation
- Google-style docstrings for APIs

## Logging
- Use loguru for structured logging
- Never use print statements for application output

## Error Handling
- Specific try-except blocks (no bare except)
- Clear, actionable error messages
- Handle edge cases explicitly

## Security
- Follow OWASP guidelines
- HTTPS in production
- Proper CORS configuration
- Sanitize all user inputs

## Dependencies
- Pin versions in requirements.txt
- Follow semantic versioning
